{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:matthew.14",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "matthew",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Matthew 14 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:1",
      "text": "At that time Herod the tetrarch heard about the fame of Jesus;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:2",
      "text": "and he said to his servants, “This is John the Baptist, he has been raised from the dead; that is why these powers are at work in him.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:3",
      "text": "For Herod had seized John and bound him and put him in prison, for the sake of Herodi-as, his brother Philip's wife;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:4",
      "text": "because John said to him, “It is not lawful for you to have her.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:5",
      "text": "And though he wanted to put him to death, he feared the people, because they held him to be a prophet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:6",
      "text": "But when Herod's birthday came, the daughter of Herodi-as danced before the company, and pleased Herod,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:7",
      "text": "so that he promised with an oath to give her whatever she might ask.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:8",
      "text": "Prompted by her mother, she said, “Give me the head of John the Baptist here on a platter.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:9",
      "text": "And the king was sorry; but because of his oaths and his guests he commanded it to be given;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:10",
      "text": "he sent and had John beheaded in the prison,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:11",
      "text": "and his head was brought on a platter and given to the girl, and she brought it to her mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:12",
      "text": "And his disciples came and took the body and buried it; and they went and told Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:13",
      "text": "Now when Jesus heard this, he withdrew from there in a boat to a lonely place apart. But when the crowds heard it, they followed him on foot from the towns.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:14",
      "text": "As he went ashore he saw a great throng; and he had compassion on them, and healed their sick.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:15",
      "text": "When it was evening, the disciples came to him and said, “This is a lonely place, and the day is now over; send the crowds away to go into the villages and buy food for themselves.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:16",
      "text": "Jesus said, “They need not go away; you give them something to eat.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:17",
      "text": "They said to him, “We have only five loaves here and two fish.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:18",
      "text": "And he said, “Bring them here to me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:19",
      "text": "Then he ordered the crowds to sit down on the grass; and taking the five loaves and the two fish he looked up to heaven, and blessed, and broke and gave the loaves to the disciples, and the disciples gave them to the crowds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:20",
      "text": "And they all ate and were satisfied. And they took up twelve baskets full of the broken pieces left over.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:21",
      "text": "And those who ate were about five thousand men, besides women and children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:22",
      "text": "Then he made the disciples get into the boat and go before him to the other side, while he dismissed the crowds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:23",
      "text": "And after he had dismissed the crowds, he went up on the mountain by himself to pray. When evening came, he was there alone,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:24",
      "text": "but the boat by this time was many furlongs distant from the land, beaten by the waves; for the wind was against them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:25",
      "text": "And in the fourth watch of the night he came to them, walking on the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:26",
      "text": "But when the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were terrified, saying, “It is a ghost!” and they cried out for fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:27",
      "text": "But immediately he spoke to them, saying, “Take heart, it is I; have no fear.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:28",
      "text": "And Peter answered him, “Lord, if it is you, bid me come to you on the water.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:29",
      "text": "He said, “Come.” So Peter got out of the boat and walked on the water and came to Jesus;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:30",
      "text": "but when he saw the wind, he was afraid, and beginning to sink he cried out, “Lord, save me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:31",
      "text": "Jesus immediately reached out his hand and caught him, saying to him, “O man of little faith, why did you doubt?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:32",
      "text": "And when they got into the boat, the wind ceased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:33",
      "text": "And those in the boat worshiped him, saying, “Truly you are the Son of God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:34",
      "text": "And when they had crossed over, they came to land at Gennesaret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:35",
      "text": "And when the men of that place recognized him, they sent round to all that region and brought to him all that were sick,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.14.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:36",
      "text": "and besought him that they might only touch the fringe of his garment; and as many as touched it were made well.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
